  <body>
    <h1>Swiftype Smart 404 Page Example</h1>

    <p>
      Welcome to the Swiftype smart 404 page example app. This application responds with a 404 for any path except this one.
    </p>

    <p>
      On the 404 page, a search is automatically executed against the Swiftype Documentation based on the URL.
      If there are results, they are shown. Either way, there is a search box for the user to find what they were looking for.
      Check out the source code of <code>views/not_found.erb</code> to see how it works.
    </p>

    <p>Try some examples:</p>

    <ul>
      <li><a href="/documentation">/documentation</a></li>
      <li><a href="/documentation/tutorials/wordpress-install-guide">/documentation/tutorials/wordpress-install-guide</a></li>
      <li><a href="/crawl-limit">/recrawl-limit</a></li>
      <li><a href="/asdf/123/foobar/baz/etc">a bunch of nonsense will not show any automatic results</a></li>
    </ul>
  </body>
</html>
